title: Photoexcitation of the 7.64-MeV Magnetic Dipole Levels in Cd112 and Ni62 by Iron Capture Gamma Rays

x4freetext: Photoexcitation of the 7.64-MeV Magnetic Dipole
Levels in Cd112 and Ni62 by Iron Capture Gamma Rays

x4freetext: The University of Virginia 1-MW reactor.
The gamma-ray source consisted of 0.5 kg of natural
iron placed near the reactor core.
The iron neutron capture gamma-rays from
56Fe(n,gamma) were used to study elastic and
inelastic scattering in Cd and Ni targets. The
capture gamma-ray beam pipe was directed tangential
to the reactor core to provide an effective shielding
of the detector against the fission gamma rays
produced in the core. The spectra of the photons
scattered from the cadmium and nickel samples were
measured with Ge(Li) and NaI detectors.
